Most of the new events were transmitted through sex, which is a change from the past.
Traditionally, HIV has spread rapidly through parts of China as a result of transfusions with infected blood.
But the number of people infected with HIV in this way has dropped to almost zero, Chinese health authorities said at a conference in Yunnan province.
From year to year, however, the number of people living with HIV and AIDS in China has grown by 100,000 people.
Transmission of HIV through sex is an acute issue of the LGBT community in China.
Homosexuality was decriminalized in China in 1997, but discrimination against people from the LGBT community is high.
Because of the country’s conservative values, research shows that 70-90% of men who have sex with men will ever marry women.
Many of the transmissions of the disease are due to inadequate sexual protection in those relationships.
Since 2003, the Chinese government has promised universal access to HIV drugs as part of efforts to address the problem.
