The population of bats in Scotland and Britain has declined significantly in the last century.
They are threatened by construction works and development that affect the beds and the loss of housing.
Windmills and lights also pose a risk, as do fly-sticks and some chemical treatments on building materials, as well as attacks on domestic cats.
The bats aren't actually blind.
